OL,3,CCouncils 'should have a say' over
OL,4,Cmigrant hotels, Lib Dem leader claims
OL,6,FIn a statement, a Home Office
OL,7,Fspokesperson said: "This government
OL,8,Finherited an asylum system in chaos,
OL,9,Fwith tens of thousands of individuals
OL,10,Fin hotels waiting for their claims to
OL,11,Fbe heard.
OL,13,F"We have taken urgent action to fix
OL,14,Fthis. This year, the rate of asylum
OL,15,Fdecision-making has doubled. We have
OL,16,Freduced spending on hotels by over
OL,17,Fhalf a billion pounds and we will
OL,18,Fclose every hotel by the end of this
OL,19,FParliament."
